Name: Florafil Shimmer Yarn
Description: Florafil Shimmer Yarn Florafil ™ Shimmer is a premium Worsted Weight Cotton Yarn with a shiny rayon boucle yarn twisted around our Super Soft Cotton roving.  This yarn has the same strength of conventional ring-spun cotton.  The colors in this collection are similar to our regular Florafil and inspired by wildflowers found across the United States.  But with a unique twist, and that is a twist of rayon boucle! The Florafil Shimmer Yarn collection includes 7 solid colors and 4 Space Dyed yarns.  Our solid colored yarns include our most popular color White Lily.  A beautiful bright white, perfect for creating a stunning bridal bolero or shrug.  In this collection we also have our Space Dyed yarns.  Coral Hibiscus is our most popular yarn from this collection.  This yarn would make a prefect sweater or wrap to dress up any occasion.  Florafil Shimmer Yarn is perfectly soft with just the right amount of elegant shine!  Ideal for any occasion that you want to create a garment that is in between casual and dressy. Our Florafil is made of cotton roving yarn.  Cotton roving allows our cotton to be closest to its natural state it is unprocessed and unspun.  There is a nylon binder as in our regular Florafil and a Rayon Boucle binder which gives this yarn its beautiful Shimmer.  The two binders also secure the roving to prevent any piling on finished projects while creating a unique twist to the yarn. Sizing: 14 stitches x 18 rows = 4” on #10 (6.5mm) needles Content: 64% Georgia Cotton, 32% Rayon, 4% Nylon Weight: 99 g / 3.5 oz Length: 114.3 m / 125 yds Care: Dry clean or hand wash in cold water. No bleach. Dry flat, do not iron. Tip: When knitting with cottons try going down a needle size to help your garments keep shape. Name: American Lamb Yarn
Description:
American Lamb Yarn

When the world outside appears as a snow globe with gentle snowflakes falling and a wintry wind blowing cuddle close to our American Lamb wool roving yarn.  Let this lofty yarn be your soothing hot cup of coffee as you face your day, and pull your merino wool sweater closer.  The wool roving and wool binding create a perfect bulky weight, soft and smooth knit fabric, utterly perfect for a chilly winter day.  Our American Lamb has a captivating texture and a soft springy feel, superb for an over-sized sweater or a beautiful cozy blanket to snuggle with next to a roaring fire.  This yarn also has a great structure and would be ideal for outwear such as knitted coats, hats, or winter accessories.

American Lamb was developed and created due to popular demand to see our Florafil Yarn in a wool version.  The strands of roving, like our Florafil Yarn, are even thickness with two binders.  This creates a strong yarn with little to no piling.  The colors are rich and deeply saturated, they look divine by themselves or mixed together in the same project.  A fantastic yarn for sweaters, coats, winter accessories, pet accessories, cup coozies, and more.

American Lamb Yarn is made from 100% U.S. grown and processed Merino Wool. With a micron count of 22 it is some of the softest American wool available.

Our sheep are raised out west of the Missouri river. Their sheared wool comes to South Carolina for carding and cleaning. The cleaned wool is sent to Rhode Island where it becomes our roving and singles. It then comes to our mill in Philadelphia where we twist and dye it. From here we distribute it to local yarn stores around the United States where you can purchase it!

Sizing: 14 stitches x 18 rows = 4” on #10 (6.5mm) needles Content: 100% American Merino Wool Weight: 100 g / 3.5 oz Length: 133 m / 146 yds Care: Dry clean or hand wash in cold water. No bleach. Dry flat, do not iron.

Name: Wayfarer Yarn
Description:
Also available on cone!

Wayfarer Yarn

Wayfarer Yarn is our collection of fingering weight wool. The yarn is twisted and dyed at our mill here in Philadelphia, PA our wool is sourced domestically.  The colors of this line were inspired by colors found in nature across the United States of America.  Coral Reef, one of our popular colors, was inspired by the marvelous purples found in the coral reefs of Florida.  Another one of our popular colors is Pine Forest this color was inspired by the majestic pine forests of Washington. Wayfarer is a lovely yarn for sock knitting because it is so soft and buttery to the touch.  It is a perfect yarn for a light weight shrug, scarf, or cape.  It is also ideal for color-work such as Fair Isle, cabling, and lace work as well.  Wayfarer yarn has a soft and bouncy hand it is truly a pleasure to work with.

 Why is our Wayfarer Yarn not a Superwashed wool?

We felt strongly about preserving the natural characteristics of the wool fiber.  We decided to offer this yarn in a non superwash, but still captured the qualities of superwash.  Our Wayfarer yarn achieves this without losing the unique characteristics that natural wool has.  We designed a special multi-twist for this merino yarn, which gives it a buttery soft and bouncy hand.  Although we understand many in the Knitting, Crocheting, and Weaving communities enjoy the ease of superwashed wool we felt that there was shortage of fingering weight wool with natural wool attributes.  This unique yarn can be used in place of any fingering weight superwash yarn.  We believe the alluring feel of natural wool was too good to superwash away!

Content: 100% wool Weight: 100 g | 3.5 oz Length: 349 m | 382 yds Care: Dry clean or hand wash in cold water. No bleach. Dry flat, do not iron.

Name: Shimmer Yarn
Description: Shimmer Yarn Florafil ™ Shimmer is a premium Worsted Weight Cotton Yarn with a shiny rayon boucle yarn twisted around our Super Soft Cotton roving.  This yarn has the same strength of conventional ring-spun cotton.  Shimmer Yarn is perfectly soft with just the right amount of elegant shine! Ideal for any occasion that you want to create a garment that is in between casual and dressy. The colors in this collection are similar to our regular Florafil and inspired by wildflowers found across the United States.  But with a unique twist, and that is a twist of rayon boucle! Sizing: 14 stitches x 18 rows = 4” on #10 (6.5mm) needles Content: 64% Georgia Cotton, 32% Rayon, 4% Nylon Weight: 200 g / 7 oz Length: 228 m / 250 yds Care: Dry clean or hand wash in cold water. No bleach. Dry flat, do not iron. Tip: When knitting with cotton try going down a needle size to help your garments keep shape.
